Mazda to Halt All Production in Thailand Until Oct. 22

-- B y   H i d e k i   A s a i
-- 
2011-10-19T04:19:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/mazda-to-halt-all-production-in-thailand-until-oct-22-correct-.html
(Corrects name of company spokesman in story published
yesterday.)  Mazda Motor Corp. (7261)  will halt
production of passenger cars in  Thailand  from tomorrow until
Oct. 22 due to a shortage of parts.  The Japanese automaker has halted production of passenger
cars during the evening shift since Oct. 13 and all production
of pick-up trucks since Oct. 11, Toyota Tanaka, a spokesman for
Mazda, said by telephone. Mazda has yet to make a decision on
production plans after Oct. 25, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hideki Asai in Tokyo at 
 hasai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  